Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @cardamom pod{1}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} in a large saucepan on medium heat. When hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, stir occasionally. Add the @korma curry paste{50%g} and half the garlic, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir and bring to the boil, add the @lamb shank{670%g} and all of the juices in the bag. Baste the lamb in the liquid using a large #spoon{} and lower the heat to a simmer.

Simmer (uncovered), basting the lamb occasionally until the sauce reduces and has thickened, ~{15-20%minutes}. Increase the heat if the sauce isn't reducing. Meanwhile, finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all) and roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Pop the coriander and peanuts in a #bowl{} and stir in the olive oil. Season with pepper and stir together - pesto done!

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir fry until the beans are slightly charred, ~{2-3%minutes}, then add the remaining garlic and @mustard seeds{1%tsp}. Stir fry for ~{1%minute}, then add a splash of water. Cover the pan with a lid or some foil, steam fry until the beans are tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Remove from the heat.

Once the lamb is cooked, season the sauce to taste with salt and pepper. Remove the cardamom pods from the rice and fluff it up with a #fork{}. Spoon the rice into one side of big #bowls{}. Carefully place the lamb on the other side of the bowl and spoon the sauce around the lamb. Finish with the green beans and then spoon the pesto over the top. Enjoy!